Zwartowo  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Choczewo, within Wejherowo County, Pomeranian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-west of Choczewo,  west of Wejherowo, and  north-west of the regional capital Gdańsk, in the historical region of Pomerania.
Polish Reformed preachers lived in the village since 1677, until the main preacher moved to nearby Lębork in 1737.
